entries.title: Navy SEAL Who Deserted in 2019 Has Been Killed in Ukraine
entries.description: The man, Daniel W. Swift, was the latest American to be killed in Ukraine, where hundreds of international volunteers have gone to fight in Ukraine’s defense.

entries.title: Allies Fail to Agree on Sending Tanks to Ukraine
entries.description: Officials tried to play down the rift. But Germany is still insisting it will not be the country to take the first step alone, for fear of incurring Moscow’s wrath.

entries.title: Chris Hipkins Poised to Replace Jacinda Ardern as New Zealand’s Leader
entries.description: Mr. Hipkins, a household name in New Zealand for his role overseeing the country’s response to the pandemic, was nominated to succeed Jacinda Ardern as leader of the governing Labour Party.

entries.title: Which Leaders Resign, Like Jacinda Ardern? Often, the System Decides.
entries.description: In parliamentary systems like New Zealand’s, it is the norm for leaders to step down when doing so may serve their party’s electoral prospects. In other political systems, leaving office early is rare.

entries.title: US to Name Wagner Mercenary Group in Russia Criminal Organization
entries.description: The move, which goes into effect next week, expands the number of nations and institutions that can be prevented from doing business with Wagner.

entries.title: Church of England Will Bless Same-Sex Couples, but Won’t Marry Them
entries.description: The policy shift comes after six years of consultations on the issue within the church, which also apologized for its treatment of L.G.B.T.Q. people.

entries.title: What Are Stryker Vehicles? And Why Are They Being Sent to Ukraine?
entries.description: The vehicles weigh about 20 tons and have eight wheels. They move quickly while carrying soldiers and can be armed with a variety of weapons.

entries.title: Western defense officials are still working to reach an agreement on providing Leopard 2 tanks to Ukraine.
Jacinda Ardern Says No to Burnout
entries.description: The New Zealand prime minister made a surprise announcement that she would step down as the country’s leader.

entries.title: Jacinda Ardern Says No to Burnout
entries.description: The New Zealand prime minister made a surprise announcement that she would step down as the country’s leader.

entries.title: A Mother in Haiti Watches Her Child’s Gang Killing
entries.description: Trapped by unending violence in the country’s largest slum, a mother makes a desperate attempt to save her teenage daughter.

entries.title: 1898: Anglo-Siberian Trade
entries.description: A Russian tariff on imports to Siberia was under discussion.

entries.title: Routine Crisis
entries.description: A political fight is again putting the economy at risk.

entries.title: Allies Pile Pressure on Germany Over Tanks for Ukraine
entries.description: Military officials from Ukraine’s allies, led by the United States, are meeting in a push to persuade Germany to provide Leopard 2 tanks or authorize other nations to do so.

entries.title: For Reporter, Trauma Comes With Exposing Ugly Truths of a Brutal Conflict
entries.description: Mariam Ouédraogo is the first female African journalist to win the world’s top prize for war correspondents, but covering the sexual violence in Burkina Faso has given her PTSD.

entries.title: Australian Man Takes 3,000-Mile Detour Because of a Flood
entries.description: Few roads crisscross Western Australia, so when a single one is closed, there can be serious complications. Ask Chris English.

entries.title: Jacinda Ardern Exits the Stage
entries.description: After the surprise had sunk in, speculation about her next move quickly began. The answer may lie in the priorities she professed before becoming prime minister.

entries.title: Jacinda Ardern Will Be Gone Soon but New Zealand’s Economic Troubles Are Here to Stay
entries.description: Ms. Ardern maneuvered through one crisis after another but had less success confronting persistent challenges that have hobbled successive governments.

entries.title: Your Friday Briefing
entries.description: A meeting in Germany of Ukraine’s allies.

entries.title: Ukraine’s Allies Pledge to Send Major Infusion of Military Aid
entries.description: As representatives from dozens of countries prepared to attend a war-planning meeting in Germany, the talk was of missiles, air defense and — above all — tanks.

entries.title: CIA Director Burns Visited Ukraine to Meet With Zelensky
entries.description: The director, William J. Burns, has made periodic visits to Ukraine to meet with intelligence officials and to exchange information to the country’s president.
